Documentation.Summary: The timestamp refers to the time the interaction took place, not to the time the record was created on the database.
Documentation.LongDescription: The timestamp must always be UTC time.When you import data, the local timestamp plus the difference to UTC is also allowed. For example, for New York local time 14:00:00, which is 5 hours before UTC, you could import the timestamp as: 2017-12-18T14:00:00-05:00 or 2017-12-18T19:00:00.When data is read, the UTC timestamp is always returned.An alternative UTC OData Format would be:Number of milliseconds since midnight Jan 1, 1970: /Date(1406014140922)/

Documentation.Summary: This field contains the complete personal name. It is usually generated from the individual name components (without title).

In this case the field CONVERTED ("Status of the field NAME_TEXT") has the value 'M'.The field CONVERTED ("Status of the field NAME_TEXT") has the value SPACE if neither of the exceptions applies.

This is a two-digit code representing a status that indicates the level of verification for a contacts information.
Documentation.LongDescription: Predelivered validation statuses and codes are:Space - Anonymous:Information about the contact is not verified. For example, there was just a click on a web site.10 - Self-Identified:The contact has entered, for example, name and address in a web form, but the information hasn't yet been verified.20 - Qualified:The contact has registered on the web site and verified the details by clicking a link in a verification email, for example.30 - Business Partner:The contact is stored in the productive SAP CRM or SAP ERP system.You cannot change the predelivered codes but you can edit the descriptive text for a status and add new validation statuses in the configuration app Validation Statuses. Validation statuses are displayed as contact levels in the Contact Profile.

Documentation.Summary: This is a status that indicates the level of verification for a contacts information.

Documentation.Summary: The country key contains information which the system uses to check entries such as the length of the postal code or bank account number.
Documentation.LongDescription: The two-character ISO code in accordance with ISO 3166, which is delivered by SAP as a default, is usually used.It could also be the vehicle license plate country-code or a typical country key, for example, in Germany the Federal statistics office key.The country keys are determined at system installation in the global settings.The definition of the country key in the SAP system does not have to match political or government entities.Since the country key does not have to correspond to the ISO code in all installations, programs that differ according to certain values of the country key cannot query the country key T005-LAND1, but have to program based on the ISO code T005 INTCA.

Documentation.Summary: In some countries, the region forms part of the address. The meaning depends on the country.
Documentation.LongDescription: The automatic address formatting function prints the region in addresses in the USA, Canada, Italy, Brazil or Australia, and the county in Great Britain.For more information, see the examples in the documentation on the Address Layout Key.Meaning of the regional code in ...Australia -> ProvinceBrazil -> StateCanada -> ProvinceGermany -> StateGreat Britain -> CountyItaly -> ProvinceJapan -> PrefectureSwitzerland -> CantonUSA -> State

Documentation.Summary: Region code of the campaign performance measures.
Documentation.LongDescription: The mapping of external values to internal codes is maintained with the Map Free Texts app.

Documentation.Summary: This is a key that represents the gender of a contact.
Documentation.LongDescription: This field contains fixed values that represent the gender of a contact. The fixed values are: 1 = Male; 2 = Female; Space = Gender not known.User-defined values can be defined in the structure CUAN_S_API_MKT_CNTCT_ORIGIN_D in SEX_FT. User-defined entries must be mapped to SAP internal keys in the Map Free Texts app.

Documentation.Summary: A free text field that specifies the gender of a contact.
Documentation.LongDescription: This field contains user-definable gender names.User-defined entries must be mapped to SAP internal keys in the Map Free Texts app.

Documentation.Summary: Postal code as part of the address
Documentation.LongDescription: If different postal codes are maintained for the PO Box and Street address of an address, this field contains the Street address postal code.

Documentation.Summary: Key for form of address text.
Documentation.LongDescription: You can also define a form of address text in Customizing.The form of address text can be maintained in different languages.

Documentation.Summary: Possible titles are stored in a check table. They are language-dependent.
Documentation.LongDescription: Choose the title from the entries in the drop down list box.The title is displayed in text form in the screen field in the logon language, and its key is stored in the database.

Documentation.Summary: This field contains the URL of a web site.
This is an alphanumeric key that identifies an industry.
Documentation.LongDescription: This field contains an alphanumber key of maximum 4 characters representing an industry.You can create custom entries in the configuration activity Industries for Contacts. User-defined values must be mapped to SAP internal keys in the Map Free Texts app.

Documentation.Summary: This field contains a free text describing the industry of your interaction contact.
Documentation.LongDescription: You can define industries for your contacts in the configuration activity Industries for Contacts. User-defined entries must be mapped to SAP internal keys in the Map Free Texts app.Examples are automotive, chemicals, energy, or construction.

Property.Name: ContactSubscriptionOriginName
Property.sap:label: Contact: Subscription Origin Name
Property.sap:heading: Description for Origin of Contact Data
Property.sap:quickinfo: Description for Origin of Interaction Contact Data

Documentation.Summary: This is a free text description of the origin.
Documentation.LongDescription: This is a read-only field.

Documentation.Summary: This is a path or channel used for communication or through which an interaction happened.
Documentation.LongDescription: Examples of communication media can be EMAIL, PHONE, WEB, and specific social media channels (to be changed!).You can configure communication media in the configuration activity Manage Interaction Content.

Documentation.Summary: This is a free text description of a communication medium.
Documentation.LongDescription: The communication medium describes the channel that a contact used to interact with your company.You can configure communication media in the configuration activity Manage Interaction Content.Examples of communication media are email, phone, text message, or social media.

Documentation.Summary: The timestamp refers to the time the interaction took place, not to the time the record was created on the database.
Documentation.LongDescription: The timestamp must always be UTC time.When you import data, the local timestamp plus the difference to UTC is also allowed. For example, for New York local time 14:00:00, which is 5 hours before UTC, you could import the timestamp as: 2017-12-18T14:00:00-05:00 or 2017-12-18T19:00:00.When data is read, the UTC timestamp is always returned.An alternative UTC OData Format would be:Number of milliseconds since midnight Jan 1, 1970: /Date(1406014140922)/

Documentation.Summary: This field indicates whether permission has been granted or not. The permission values can be Y (Yes) or N (No).
A grouping defined to manage newsletter subscriptions and communication limits for use in marketing campaigns.
Documentation.LongDescription: A communication category can be assigned to an email or text message marketing campaign. It determines, for example, if contacts can subscribe or unsubscribe to newsletters or events using a landing page.When you create a newsletter subscription, the response of this request also contains the newsletter subscription name in the property.

Documentation.Summary: The name of a communication category. A communication category is a grouping to manage newsletter subscriptions for marketing campaigns.
The ID of the result object, for example, material number.
A recommendation data source type that is defined to an ITEM data source class, for example, SAP Commerce Product.
Documentation.LongDescription: You can use the ItemSourceType entity to enable your customer channel to choose BasketObjectType from a value help.

Documentation.Summary: This field contains the type of source system from which the interaction data came.
Documentation.LongDescription: The source system type identifies the type of system in which the interaction occurred. Types of source system include web shops, C4C systems or clickstream monitoring tools.

Documentation.Summary: This is a path or channel used to indicate from which communication medium a permission or subscription has been created.
Documentation.LongDescription: You can configure communication media in the configuration app Manage Interaction Content or in Customizing for SAP Marketing under Interactions -> Define Communication Media. Examples of communication media can be EMAIL, PHONE, WEB.

Documentation.Summary: This is a free text description of a communication medium.
Documentation.LongDescription: The communication medium describes the channel that a contact used to interact with your company.You can configure communication media in the configuration activity Manage Interaction Content.Examples of communication media are email, phone, text message, or social media.

Documentation.Summary: This is an indicator showing if a confirmation is required before storing the permission or subscription.
Documentation.LongDescription: If the parameter is set to TRUE, the permission is stored using the double opt-in or opt-out process.If the property is not specified in the payload or it is set to FALSE the permission is directly stored.

Documentation.Summary: This field contains the complete personal name. It is usually generated from the individual name components (without title).
Documentation.LongDescription: There are two exceptions:The field contents were assembled by converting data from a previous release from the previous title and name fields because the title could not be assigned automatically to a title key . In this case the field CONVERTED ("Status of the field NAME_TEXT") has the value 'X'.The field contents were maintained manually using a supplementary function in dialog, e.g. because the complete name cannot be split into the specified name parts. In this case the field CONVERTED ("Status of the field NAME_TEXT") has the value 'M'.The field CONVERTED ("Status of the field NAME_TEXT") has the value SPACE if neither of the exceptions applies.
